Pretoria - An alleged fugitive was shot dead during a shootout with police on Thursday afternoon in Mattafin, Nelspruit. According to Mpumalanga police spokesperson Selvy Mohlala, police received information about a fugitive spotted in Mattafin.  “The suspect, identified as Bheki Martin Phiri, 28, was wanted for escaping from lawful custody on 11 November, 2022 as well as for a case of attempted murder where a police sergeant, 40, was shot and wounded by the suspect on 22 December, 2022.” After police got information of his whereabouts, they drove to the said place. On arrival, Phiri reportedly noticed the officers and opened fire  on them. “They responded accordingly and defended themselves, whereby the suspect was fatally shot. A firearm as well as live ammunition were found next  to the suspect. He was certified dead at the scene by the paramedics.” Mohlala said a case of murder was opened and the Independent Police Investigative Directorate will conduct further investigations. IOL